div.div: The sequel to the 'Final Season' story arc of the Monogatari series. From the past to the future, their story continues. Now that he has graduated from high school, Koyomi Araragi’s story ends here. His story is truly over now, but the stories of the girls Koyomi saved - their stories - are not over yet. This is the prequel or sequel to their stories and their struggles. (Source: Monogatari Series USA Official Website) Note: Relations are provisional and subject to change.
Akuyaku Reijou Level 99: Watashi wa Ura Boss desu ga Maou de wa Arimasen

This college kid wants nothing more than a quiet life. So when she’s reborn as Yumiella, the hidden villainess of an Otome RPG, she’s not exactly thrilled. Still yearning for peace, she abandons her evil duties to live a more discreet life. Until her gamer side kicks in and she accidentally reaches level 99! Now, everyone suspects that she’s the infamous Demon Lord. What future awaits her?
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Jimi de Medatanai Watashi wa, Kyou de Owari ni Shimasu.

Elaine Lana Norris, who was born at the top of the aristocratic ladder, was suddenly abandoned by her fiancé for another and had her engagement to him broken off. Made out to be a villainess by her ex-fiancé's lover and her entourage, she is subsequently driven out of her home by the strict grandfather who raised her. With this exiled life however, Lana's true skills and desires can finally bloom as the owner of an inn!

Leticia Dorman is living every girl’s dream—she’s the daughter of a duke who’s grown up in the lap of luxury and she’s engaged to none other than the handsome crown prince, Clarke. But this dream is her nightmare! In preparation to become part of the royal family, Lettie has endured ten painful years of lessons on everything from dancing to etiquette. Her only chance of escape lies in the prince breaking off their engagement, which seems unlikely…until he shows up at a royal ball with a mysterious woman. This could be her chance to break free, but not if Prince Clarke has anything to say about it!
(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)
